# Dormant Hypotheses

## 0. Role Of This File

This file stores set-aside ideas and the conditions that would revive them. These should not be active by default, but should not be forgotten either. Active candidates live in `docs/project/backlog/active-issues.md`; approaches ruled out for good belong in `docs/method/algorithmic-levers.md` and are not revived without new evidence. Dormant differs from rejected: a dormant idea is plausible but not worth pursuing yet, whereas a rejected one has evidence against it.

## 1. Dormant Ideas

For each idea, record why it is parked and the concrete condition that would bring it back, so a future session can tell at a glance whether the moment has arrived. The row below is a marked example.

| hypothesis | why dormant | revive condition |
|---|---|---|
| (example) try an alternative model family | too costly to justify before a baseline exists | revisit once the baseline is established and its limits are known |

Keep the revive condition specific and checkable ("once metric X plateaus below 0.8"), not vague ("if we have time"). Review this list when a major result lands -- a new finding can move an idea from here to `docs/project/backlog/active-issues.md`.
